    <div id="block-faqaccueil-en" class="contextual-region block-faqaccueil block block-views">
      
          <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div data-contextual-id="block:block=faqaccueil_en:langcode=en|entity.view.edit_form:view=blocs_de_l_accueil:location=block&amp;name=blocs_de_l_accueil&amp;display_id=block_2&amp;langcode=en"></div>
        <div class="views-element-container"><div class="faq-4-items view">
  
    
        <p><a class="button" href="/en/advices/faq">All frequently asked questions</a></p>

      
      <div class="view-content">
        <div class="views-row" id="271">
    <div class="views-field views-field-title"><span class="field-content"><a href="/en/advices/faq#271">Should I complain or report?</a></span></div><div class="views-field views-field-body"><div class="field-content">A complaint to the Québec Ombudsman is usually filed by the person who personally experienced the situation for which the complaint was lodged while a report is made by someone who has witnessed shortcomings or injustice in public services.</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-nid-1"><span class="field-content"><a href="/en/advices/faq#271" class="white-button">Read more <span class="visuallyhidden">Should I complain or report?</span></a></span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="views-row" id="1258">
    <div class="views-field views-field-title"><span class="field-content"><a href="/en/advices/faq#1258">I can’t seem to be able to attach documents to my complaint form or document transmission form. Why?</a></span></div><div class="views-field views-field-body"><div class="field-content">Check your browser. The Québec Ombudsman’s site is designed to function with most PC or Mac browsers. We recommend that you always use the latest version for speedy web page display. </div></div><div class="views-field views-field-nid-1"><span class="field-content"><a href="/en/advices/faq#1258" class="white-button">Read more <span class="visuallyhidden">I can’t seem to be able to attach documents to my complaint form or document transmission form. Why?</span></a></span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="views-row" id="273">
    <div class="views-field views-field-title"><span class="field-content"><a href="/en/advices/faq#273">Do I have to give out my personal contact information when I file a complaint?</a></span></div><div class="views-field views-field-body"><div class="field-content">Yes. Section 20 of the Public Protector Act specifies that every person who applies to have the Québec Ombudsman intervene must give his or her name, address and telephone number.</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-nid-1"><span class="field-content"><a href="/en/advices/faq#273" class="white-button">Read more <span class="visuallyhidden">Do I have to give out my personal contact information when I file a complaint?</span></a></span></div>
  </div>
  <div class="views-row" id="277">
    <div class="views-field views-field-title"><span class="field-content"><a href="/en/advices/faq#277">Can I file a complaint if I am not a Canadian citizen or Québec resident?</a></span></div><div class="views-field views-field-body"><div class="field-content">Yes. You can ask the Québec Ombudsman for its help even if you are not a Canadian citizen or have permanent resident status.</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-nid-1"><span class="field-content"><a href="/en/advices/faq#277" class="white-button">Read more <span class="visuallyhidden">Can I file a complaint if I am not a Canadian citizen or Québec resident?</span></a></span></div>
